My latest empi muffler that has failed, empi won't replace!  They said it failed because I installed it myself and it wasn't installed by the shop where I purchased it.  Saying that if I had used the hanger properly, it would not have failed.  The Ironic thing about that statement is the hanger clamp they provided me the first time would no way fit around the extractor tube and be in a position that I could bolt it to the hanger as recommended.  So when empi replaced it, the did not provide the hanger clamp and provided instead a band clamp.  Now the band clamp, which goes around the extractor tube and through the welded  hanger on muffler, has pulled the seam apart on the muffler!  So they are now selling a product that they can't stand behind or replace under a 90 day warranty!
 
Also I have gone through a set empi carb filters for my dellorto's.  They have both failed at the tack weld on the base plate of the filter assembly.  I had to tig weld them back together and they have broken again in a different place.  My welds held, their steel didn't!  Empi won't replace this either.  I am fortunate that none of the pieces of these lame ass filter assemblies did not fall into my cylinders and destroy a new engine!
 
Paul

