I don't mind (and don't buy) the junk tools and products that fill the
blister packs in the $1 Stores or Odd Lot Stores... But what irks me
is the use of "real" names on products that fall apart even when I've
made a point to purchase something I thought was a quality product.
I've given up faulting the factory/country where the product is made,
since it seems to be a total lack of any concern by the mother com-
pany for quality control over products that carry their name. I can't
believe "competition" is so fierce over these products, that price is 
the only factor...I wonder if the profit margin is so great with these
inferior products, that it doesn't matter how many come back or have
to be replaced... ?-(

